Property Description <code>self.active_request</code> Current HTTP request (via ContextVar) — available in any model method called during a request <code>self.active_request.DATA</code> Unified dict of all request data (POST body + GET params) <code>self.active_user</code> Current authenticated user (<code>self.active_request.user</code>) <p><code>self.active_request</code> is set automatically by the framework at the start of every REST request and is accessible from any model method — lifecycle hooks, <code>set_&lt;field&gt;</code> methods, <code>on_action_&lt;name&gt;</code> handlers, etc. Use it instead of threading request through every method call:</p> <pre><code>def on_rest_saved(self, changed_fields, created):
    request = self.active_request
    if request and "status" in changed_fields:
        notify_status_change(self, user=request.user)

def on_action_resend(self, value):
    lang = self.active_request.DATA.get("lang", "en")
    send_notification(self, lang=lang)
    return {"status": True}
</code></pre>

